<h1 class="flex items-center font-sans font-bold break-normal text-indigo-500 px-2 py-8 text-xl md:text-2xl">
    Security Rules
</h1>
<h2 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-dark">Geologists in the laboratory often work with rock, soil, mineral and fluid samples, as well as potentially hazardous chemicals. Therefore, it is important for them to follow strict safety rules to prevent accidents. Here are some of the most important safety rules for geologists in the laboratory:</h2>
<ol class=" space-y-1 text-gray-500 list-decimal list-inside dark:text-gray-800">
    <li><span class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-black">Use of personal protective equipment: </span>Geologists in the laboratory must wear personal protective equipment such as lab coats, gloves, protective eyewear, and respirator masks to protect themselves against harmful substances and physical hazards.</li>
    <li><span class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-black">Knowledge of chemicals:</span>Geologists in the laboratory must know the properties and risks of the chemicals they use, as well as appropriate handling and disposal procedures.</li>
    <li><span class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-black">Correct use of equipment and tools: </span> Geologists in the laboratory must use equipment and tools correctly to avoid accidents. They must also ensure that equipment is used in the conditions for which it was designed.</li>
    <li><span class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-black">Respect for emergency procedures: </span>Geologists in the laboratory must know the emergency procedures in case of an accident and follow them strictly to minimize injuries and damages.</li>
    <li><span class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-black">Communication and collaboration:  </span>  Geologists in the laboratory must communicate regularly and collaborate closely to ensure the safety of all team members. They must report potential hazards and work together to find solutions to reduce risks.</li>
    <li><span class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-black">Cleaning and storage: </span>  Geologists in the laboratory must clean work surfaces and store equipment and chemicals appropriately to avoid accidents.</li>
</ol>
<h2 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-dark">It is important to follow these safety rules to minimize the risks of accidents in geological laboratories.</h2>

